description: A findings domain that contains data related to the structure, function, evolution, mapping, and editing of subject and non-host organism genomic material of interest. This domain includes but is not limited to assessments and results for genetic variation and transcription, and summary measures derived from these assessments. The GF domain is used for findings from characteristics assessed from nucleic acids and may include subsequent inferences and/or predictions about related proteins/amino acids.
label: Genomics Findings
name: GF
